## Q9: How do you isolate interface-level network errors, packet drops, or collisions on a specific NIC?
"I check low-level interface statistics using `ip -s link show <interface>` (such as `eth0`) or the `ethtool` command. I look specifically at the `errors`, `dropped`, and `overrun` counters under the receive (RX) and transmit (TX) sections. A high number of drops or errors usually points to physical cabling issues, bad switch port configurations, or a network ring buffer saturation."

